data.text:
Diana Gurtskaya is a Russian singer who began her career in 2000. Affected by visual impairment since birth, to date she has released six studio albums, two compilation albums and several singles and has recorded duets with various well-known foreign singers including Ray Charles, Toto Cutugno and Demis Roussos.

She was selected to represent Georgia in the Eurovision Song Contest 2008 in Belgrade with the song "Peace Will Come", which successfully qualified from the second semi-final, finishing in 11th place with 83 points.
